Package cu.edu.cujae.graphy.core.iterators

Interface GraphIterator<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractGraphIterator
    public interface GraphIterator<T>
extends java.util.Iterator<T>
    A graph iterator is a special kind of iterator that allows random traversal of a graph. It extends the functionality found in Iterator, but does not replace it. One can still use a GraphIterator as a regular Iterator.
    Author:
    Javier Marrero

      • getLabel

        int getLabel()
        Each node in a graph is somehow labeled. In this library, labels are integer indices that are unique to each node in the graph. This method should return the node's label of the node it is currently standing over.
        Returns:
